power loss when accelerating or reversing

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the retainer clip can cause metal shards to damage the rear end, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause a loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to turn the wheel, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion assembly can cause a loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to turn the wheel, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect steering geometry can cause the tire to rub against the lower control arm, leading to tire failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

the steering needs to be centered.
